predict_diagnosis:
1. Syndromes associated with triplication of chromosome 16 (such as Prader-Willi syndrome, Angelman syndrome, and Smith-Magenis syndrome)
2. Congenital adrenal hyperplasia (CAH)
3. Cornelia de Lange syndrome (also known as Cockayne-Lange syndrome)
4. 22q11.2 Deletion syndrome (also known as DiGeorge syndrome)
5. Down syndrome
6. Congenitally corrected transposition of the great arteries (ccTGA)
7. Rett syndrome
8. Kartagener syndrome
9. Sickle cell anemia
10. Non-syndrome growth restriction and delayed development (also known as constitutional small stature or growth delay)
